author: Doug Randall
title: Laramie, Cheyenne Had First And Second Warmest September Ever
text: Laramie had it's warmest September on record last month while Cheyenne had it second warmest, according to the Cheyenne Office of the National Weather Servic e. The agency posted the following on its website; More Warm Weather Expected Cheyenne Forecast Tonight Mostly clear, with a low around 36. East southeast wind around 10 mph becoming south southwest after midnight. Friday Sunny, with a high near 80. South southwest wind 10 to 15 mph. Friday Night Clear, with a low around 47. South southwest wind 10 to 15 mph becoming west after midnight. Saturday Sunny, with a high near 81. Breezy, with a west wind 15 to 20 mph increasing to 20 to 25 mph in the afternoon. Winds could gust as high as 40 mph. Saturday Night Clear, with a low around 38. Northwest wind 10 to 15 mph becoming northwest 5 to 10 mph after midnight. Sunday Sunny, with a high near 74.
